  "prompt": "What is a list of formula sheets for each subject for the GATE in mechanical to cope with last minute preparation?",
  "response": "Preparing for the GATE (Graduate Aptitude Test in Engineering) in Mechanical Engineering requires a solid grasp of fundamental concepts and formulas across various subjects. Below is a list of **key formula sheets** for each subject to help with last-minute preparation:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Engineering Mathematics**\n- Linear Algebra: Matrix operations, Eigenvalues, Eigenvectors\n- Calculus: Limits, Continuity, Differentiation, Integration, Maxima/Minima, Taylor Series\n- Differential Equations: First-order ODEs, Higher-order ODEs, Laplace Transforms\n- Probability and Statistics: Mean, Variance, Probability Distributions, Bayes' Theorem\n\n---\n\n### **2. Applied Mechanics and Design**\n- **Statics**: Equilibrium of forces, Moments, Trusses, Friction\n- **Dynamics**: Kinematics, Kinetics, Work-Energy Principle, Impulse-Momentum\n- **Strength of Materials**: Stress-Strain, Bending Moment, Shear Force, Torsion, Buckling\n- **Vibrations**: Free and Forced Vibrations, Damping, Natural Frequency\n- **Machine Design**: Design of Shafts, Gears, Bearings, Fasteners, Springs\n\n---\n\n### **3. Fluid Mechanics and Thermal Sciences**\n- **Fluid Mechanics**: Bernoulli's Equation, Continuity Equation, Flow through pipes, Laminar and Turbulent flow\n- **Thermodynamics**: Laws of Thermodynamics, Heat Engines, Refrigeration, Entropy, Properties of Pure Substances\n- **Heat Transfer**: Conduction, Convection, Radiation, Heat Exchangers, Fourier's Law, Stefan-Boltzmann Law\n\n---\n\n### **4. Materials, Manufacturing, and Industrial Engineering**\n- **Engineering Materials**: Stress-Strain curves, Hardness, Crystal Structures, Phase Diagrams\n- **Manufacturing Processes**: Casting, Welding, Machining, Forming, Material Removal Rate\n- **Metrology and Inspection**: Tolerance, Fits, Gauges, Surface Roughness\n- **Operations Research**: Linear Programming, PERT-CPM, Queuing Theory\n- **Production Planning and Inventory Control**: EOQ, Break-even Analysis\n\n---\n\n### **5. General Aptitude**\n- **Verbal Ability**: Synonyms, Antonyms, Sentence Completion, Grammar\n- **Numerical Ability**: Arithmetic, Algebra, Geometry, Probability\n\n---\n\n### **Tips for Last-Minute Preparation:**\n1. Focus on **high-weightage topics** (e.g., Thermodynamics, Strength of Materials, Manufacturing).\n2. Revise **shortcut formulas** and standard results.\n3. Practice **previous years' questions** to understand pattern and important concepts.\n4. Keep a **handwritten formula sheet** for quick revision.\n\nThese formula sheets will help you streamline your preparation and focus on the most critical aspects of each subject. Good luck! \ud83d\ude80",
